# TODO

## Redirections

The taskmaster should be able to redirect the stdout and stderr of the managed processes to log files. This can be achieved by using the `os/exec` package in Go, which allows us to set the `Stdout` and `Stderr` fields of the `Cmd` struct to file handles.

We need to account for file handling: create log files if they don't exist, error management if trying to write to a file that can't be accessed, etc.

## Reload: subtle cases

According to the supervisor documentation, sending `SIGHUP` to the daemon will trigger a blind stop of all programs followed by a reload of the first configuration file found. Autostart programs will be restarted after the reload.

We need to be more considerate in our implementation of the reload command, as the subject requires us to only stop programs that have been modified. This is easily done doing a diff between old and new conf files.

There are some edge cases to consider though:

- Adding more subprocesses to an existing program: we should only start the new subprocesses, not the whole program.
- Removing subprocesses from an existing program: we should only stop the removed subprocesses, not the whole program.
- Changing any other parameter of an existing program (command, environment variables, working directory, etc.): we should stop the whole program and start it again with the new configuration.

## Restart

I was going to trash the restart command, but the subject actually seems to require it, so I guess we'll have to implement it. It should be straightforward: kill the program and start it again with the same configuration. We can reuse the existing stop and start functions for this so I don't expect much more code to be added here.
